Name Period 4 includes the biologically essential elements potassium and calcium , and is the first period in the d - block with the lighter transition metals .
These include iron , the heaviest element forged in main - sequence stars and a principal component of the Earth , as well as other important metals such as cobalt , nickel , and copper .
Almost all have biological roles .
Completing the fourth period are the post - transition metals zinc and gallium , the metalloids germanium and arsenic , and the nonmetals selenium , bromine , and krypton . PERIOD 5 Section::::Period 5 . !
