18 !
Name Period 5 has the same number of elements as period 4 and follows the same general structure but with one more post transition metal and one fewer nonmetal .
Of the three heaviest elements with biological roles , two ( molybdenum and iodine ) are in this period ; tungsten , in period 6 , is heavier , along with several of the early lanthanides .
Period 5 also includes technetium , the lightest exclusively radioactive element .
